   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project mainly contributes to results within Combating gender based violence. Results will be reported later in the Global Civsam grant period 2016-2020</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Women&amp;rsquo;s Development Centre (WDC) is an organisation that assists women and children who are victims of violence and marginalized because of their disability. &amp;nbsp;WDC strives to empower them through access to knowledge, encourage economic independence and contribute to strengthening women socially, including improving their standard of living. The goal is to create a society where women are actively involved, have equal opportunity and access to resources and control over their lives.
WDC&amp;rsquo;s activities have gradually broadened to include crisis intervention, community based rehabilitation, health and counselling, skilled development for women and youth. Mobilization is through an extensive network of women&amp;rsquo;s groups that engage in intervention, prevention and advocacy efforts at grass root and national level. &amp;nbsp;The Network is also the conduit through which communities are educated on prevention of GBV, child rights and related services for women and youth oppressed or marginalized by society. WDC&amp;rsquo;s experience has proven that it is not substantial to work with women only, but to involve men and boys in their efforts to combat violence against women and gender-based violence.&amp;nbsp;
WDC strives to extend and expand their coverage and outreach of influence in all districts of the island, and include groups at risk &amp;ndash; i.e. women sex workers and their children; women and children in the plantation estates; direct and indirect war affected women. The effort also contribute to empower and support women in decision-making positions, such as political representation.
Thematic area Gender equality, Conflict and justice, and protection of the environment.</narrative>
  </description>
